ALONZO KING, Choreographer:
My name is Alonzo King.

00:20.866 --> 00:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm the artistic director
of Alonzo King LINES Ballet.

00:24.533 --> 00:27.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a San Francisco-based
international touring
ballet company.

00:27.700 --> 00:32.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were invited to the Health
Festival here at Aspen, and
I brought four dancers from

00:34.766 --> 00:39.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the company to do a
demonstration and talk
about how health and
art are intertwined.

00:40.633 --> 00:44.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
My mother took
dancing at university.

00:44.566 --> 00:49.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when I was a kid, she would
show me things, and I had a
blast with intimacy with my mom.

00:50.766 --> 00:55.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Plus, I loved moving,
so I never stopped.

00:55.200 --> 01:00.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a triumvirate of
body/mind/soul that is in
a balancing act for health.

01:05.333 --> 01:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If something is imbalanced, then
it's with - - it's dis-eased.

01:12.266 --> 01:16.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
